    "A perpendicular static field keeps the point group unchanged, so the set of symmetry-allowed tensor components is the same.",
    "What changes is the built-in layer asymmetry.",
    "The stacking already produces an intrinsic potential difference between the two layers.",
    "Depending on its sign, the external field can either reinforce the built-in polarity or counteract it.",
    "These competing contributions allow the shift conductivity to be tuned in opposite directions, and in some cases the effective asymmetry can be significantly reduced."
